
Draft for game/simulator ardbus-console communication
-----------------------------------------------------

consoles are inited with: 
python ardubridge.py console_config.cfg 

Ardbubridge is signal wrapper generator that uses
console configuration file to map event signals from 
simulator and game components into low level commands 
that ardubus uses to communicate with actual arduino based 
console panels. It also provides mapping of switches and other 
user input from consoles into meaningfull signals to command 
the simulator.

All signals from simulator are in format 
singal_name(item_index, value, ...)

inputs section specifies how to map signals.
format is:
signal_name=action_method, group start index, real lowest value, real highest value 
parameters are optional

example:
generator_speed=set_servo, 10, 0, 10000
generator_temp=set_servo, 15, 25, 250

simulator wants to display speed of generators 1, and 2
it signals: 
fi.hacklab.ardubus.generator_speed(0, 8000)
fi.hacklab.ardubus.generator_speed(1, 2000)

proper commands for servors at index 10 and 11
will be called:
ardubus.set_servo(10, 144)
ardubus.set_servo(11, 36)

